Here is exactly what that choice means and the route you should take to keep moving fast:

🚀 Choose: "Build in the Dashboard" (Highly Recommended)
For a hackathon MVP, do not select the MPC track.

Why you should skip MPC right now:
MPC (Multi-Party Computation) setup is for advanced, enterprise-grade key management. It requires you to configure independent node committees or utilize complex SDK integrations to split and manage raw private cryptographic keys. Trying to build an MPC infrastructure from scratch over a weekend will consume 90% of your hacking time and leave you with no working frontend.

Why you should choose Dashboard:
"Build in the Dashboard" means you are using World's hosted infrastructure (cloud actions) and standard Web3 connection widgets (like IDKit or standard WalletConnect providers).

It gives you an instant, user-friendly UI component.

It lets you configure your staging environment, generate your verification QR codes, and track success logs entirely through their web interface.

It easily hands off the verification data to your frontend so you can immediately route it to NameStone or Hedera.

Your Exact Next Moves in the Dashboard:
Once you click "Build in the Dashboard", do these three things to clear Step 1:

Create an App: Name your project Satoshi's ParaBox.

Create an Action: Look for the "Actions" tab and create a new one. Name it something like user-login. Set the action type to Cloud.

Copy your Credentials: The dashboard will generate an App ID (usually looks like app_xxxx...) and an Action ID (e.g., user-login). Grab both of these—you will drop them directly into your frontend code to initialize the login popup.

Once you have those IDs copied, your portal config is done, and you are ready to start writing the code that triggers the popup!

