In World ID, the identifier ensures that a user's anonymity is preserved across different actions. When a user scans their QR code, World ID uses this identifier to generate a unique cryptographic proof.

This means:

If a user logs into your app using the user-login action, they get a specific anonymous user ID.

If you create a second action later called delete-data, the system will generate a completely different anonymous ID for that same user.

This prevents anyone from tracking a user’s behavior across different parts of your application, which fits perfectly into the high-privacy narrative of Satoshi’s ParaBox!

