I got this message. "RP registration is not active. Please ensure your app is properly registered."

This is a common error message when setting up World ID for the first time, and it is usually caused by a slight desync between your local code and the developer portal settings.

"RP" stands for Relying Party, which is the cryptographic term for your application. This error simply means World ID's servers are rejecting the login request because the configuration IDs in your code don't perfectly match the active Action you just created in the dashboard.

Here is how to fix it in two minutes:

1. Check your Environment Mode (Staging vs. Production)
Because you selected Managed and Generate New Key, your action defaults to a specific environment.

